      "description": "Offering a driver-focused 2008 BMW M3 (E92) powered by the high-revving S65 4.0L V8, featuring individual throttle bodies and an 8,400 RPM redline. This example is equipped with the sought-after 6-speed longitudinal manual transmission and a variable M differential lock for optimal power delivery. The chassis retains its composure via an aluminum multi-link suspension setup, providing precise turn-in and high-speed stability. Recent preventative maintenance includes rod bearing replacement and throttle actuator service, ensuring the internal reciprocating assembly is within spec. The exterior maintains a sharp profile, while the interior displays minor bolster wear typical of a well-driven performance machine. A mechanically robust specimen for the purist who values the last naturally aspirated M-car.",
